---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import NineDots from "../../components/NineDots.astro";

const services = [
  {
    cat: "Communication",
    name: "See People Clearly",
    body: "A two-part Enneagram workshop. Your team learns themselves first, then each other. Most companies start here.",
    href: "/professional-work/see-people-clearly",
    sig: "#006073",
  },
  {
    cat: "Leadership",
    name: "Manage With Meaning",
    body: "Practical leadership training. Managers learn to build accountability, coach their people, and give honest feedback.",
    href: "/professional-work/manage-with-meaning",
    sig: "#9C1B30",
  },
  {
    cat: "Teams",
    name: "Team Effectiveness",
    body: "Not a stock curriculum. Built around what your team is actually working through.",
    href: "/professional-work/team-effectiveness",
    sig: "#D57A27",
  },
  {
    cat: "Support",
    name: "Workplace Support",
    body: "Confidential support, mediation, and facilitated conversations for the people issues that need more than another meeting.",
    href: "/professional-work/workplace-support",
    sig: "#2BA1A3",
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="Professional Work · Ennea Evolution"
  description="Build a team that works well together. Enneagram workshops, manager development, and workplace support. Learning and laughter go together here."
>
  <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero split: copy left, photo right -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container split" style="align-items:center;">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Professional Work</p>
        <h1>Build a team that works <em>well</em> together.</h1>
        <p class="lead">I bring the Enneagram, and a genuinely different kind of experience, to your team. Learning and laughter go together here, and that's what a day with Ennea Evolution feels like.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:1rem;">Let's Talk</a>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-slot" style="--tint:var(--t1);">
        <span>Photo: real workshop candid. The room mid-laugh, or Candace teaching with visible energy</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #FFF7E7 · quote band -->
  <section class="panel-tight tint-band" style="--tint:#FFF7E7;">
    <div class="container">
      <blockquote class="pullquote" style="margin-block:1rem;">
        [ Attendee quote to come ]
        <cite>Name, role, team size</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 3 · white · narrow aside, thin teal left rule -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="aside-rule">
        <h3>About the word "I"</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0;">You'll see a lot of I on these pages, and I want to say why. This isn't about me. It's about you. I trust that you want something real, so I'm not going to hide behind a corporate we. It's me you're going to get.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 4 · white · 50/50 split: photo left, copy right -->
  <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="photo-slot" style="--tint:var(--t1);">
        <span>Photo: over-the-shoulder of participants at a table covered in type tiles and cards. Hands, materials, engagement</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>What you're getting</h3>
        <p>A workshop with your team engaged in real conversation, real laughter, and people leaning into the ideas they can use right away.</p>
        <p>This is a training where your team learns why they work the way they do, and why the people around them work completely differently. That's where most misunderstanding starts, and it's where it stops.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote gold-underline" style="margin-block:1.5rem 0;"><span class="uq">Fun in the room. Real change after.</span></blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 5 · white -->
  <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>How it works</h3>
      <p>I use the Enneagram. It's a personality assessment, and one people love taking, because it finally explains the thing everyone's quietly curious about: why they're the way they are.</p>
      <p>That's the hook. The depth is what we do with it. On its own, knowing your type is a fun fact. When your team learns this together, they stop guessing about each other and start seeing what's going on: in meetings, in conflict, in the handoffs where things usually break.</p>
      <p>It's the lens and language a team learns to use with each other. And it's where the name Ennea Evolution comes from.</p>
      <p><em>Curious about the Enneagram itself? There's a page for that. <a href="/enneagram">The Enneagram →</a></em></p>

      <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">Where it helps</h3>
      <p>You don't need a crisis to do this. Most teams have friction they've just stopped addressing.</p>
      <p>Maybe people communicate past each other, or a new manager is learning to lead. Maybe you're heading into change, or two good people just cannot figure each other out.</p>
      <p>None of it means anything's wrong with anyone. It's what happens when smart people work together without a shared way of understanding each other. This gives them that, and the tools to use it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 6 · tint #E9F3F1 · card grid, 4 across -->
  <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#E9F3F1;">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">How we can work together</h3>
      <div class="grid-4">
        {services.map((s) => (
          <a href={s.href} class="card" style={`--rule:${s.sig};`}>
            <p class="card-cat">{s.cat}</p>
            <p class="card-title" style="font-size:1.12rem;">{s.name}</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom:0;">{s.body}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      <div class="center" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <h4>Start where it makes sense</h4>
        <p style="max-width:52ch; margin-inline:auto; margin-bottom:0;">Every company starts somewhere different. Pick the one that fits what you're after. We'll build from there.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 7 · white · 50/50 split: copy left, photo right -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container split">
      <div>
        <h3>Why me</h3>
        <p>Half my week is one-on-one with people, up close, under real pressure. So none of this is theory. I watch how people really operate, then bring it into your building.</p>
        <p>I've taught this in research labs, medical offices, software companies, and event organizations. The setting changes. People don't. Because there's no such thing as just business. There's only life, and a good share of it happens at work, in the company you keep.</p>
        <p>Teams at Modern Expo, the Small Satellite Conference, Plan to Eat, and Power Driven Diesel have brought this to their organizations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-slot" style="--tint:var(--t1);">
        <span>Photo: Candace candid, teaching or in conversation, warm and confident</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 8 · white · logo band -->
  <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container center">
      <h4>Some of the teams I've worked with</h4>
      <div class="logo-row">
        <img src="/img/logos/hlo-lighting.png" alt="HLO Lighting" />
        <img src="/img/logos/m-squared.png" alt="M Squared" />
        <img src="/img/logos/spot-on.png" alt="Spot On" />
        <img src="/img/logos/allways.png" alt="Allways" />
        <img src="/img/logos/pro-green-supply.png" alt="Pro Green Supply" />
        <img src="/img/logos/total-tree-care.png" alt="Total Tree Care" />
        <img src="/img/logos/acer-trees.png" alt="Acer Trees Utah" />
        <img src="/img/logos/lg-collective.png" alt="LG Collective" />
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top:2.25rem;"><NineDots /></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 9 · white · centered close -->
  <section class="panel center" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>Bring this to your team</h3>
      <p>Tell me a little about your team. I'll tell you whether I can help, and what it would look like.</p>
      <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Let's Talk</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .logo-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
  .logo-row img {
    height: 40px;
    width: auto;
    filter: grayscale(1);
    opacity: 0.6;
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
  }
</style>
